channel.title: Error while TURNING ON server?
channel.description: Okay, i got this message when I try to turn on my server. [code]Your server is now online. Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: "5 11 " at java.lang.NumberFormatException.forInputString(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Unknown Source) at NPCHandler.loadAutoSpawn(NPCHandler.java:1996) at NPCHandler.<init>(NPCHandler.java:550) at server.main(server.java:164) [/code] Can anyone please help me?

item.title: Error while TURNING ON server?
item.dc:creator: @king_gauge king gauge
item.description:
@king_gauge wrote:

This is because of the Cache (or atleast that’s what someone told me). You go to the C:/ drive and Make a new folder named “508 Cache” (without quotes) inside you put the runescape cache folder in it. (You only need to play runescape once to get that) It will be in your C:/ drive also. Hope this helped you.
